## Codex Brief 3: Telegram Alerts (Feature 7)

### Context
You are building a Supabase Edge Function that sends Telegram notifications when signal statuses change. It triggers via a Supabase database webhook on the `signal_history` table.

### Prerequisites
- Supabase project with `signal_history` table (Feature 1)
- Telegram bot token + chat ID (from @BotFather)

### What to Build

**1. `supabase/functions/signal-alert/index.ts`:**

```typescript
import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";

const TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = Deno.env.get("TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN")!;
const TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = Deno.env.get("TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID")!;
const WEBHOOK_SECRET = Deno.env.get("WEBHOOK_SECRET")!;

const STATUS_EMOJI = {
  green: "🟢",
  amber: "🟡",
  red: "🔴",
};

const DOMINO_NAMES = {
  1: "SaaS Compression",
  2: "White-Collar Displacement",
  3: "Friction Collapse",
  4: "Ghost GDP",
  5: "Financial Contagion",
  6: "Policy Response",
};

serve(async (req) => {
  // Verify webhook origin
  const authHeader = req.headers.get("Authorization");
  if (authHeader !== `Bearer ${WEBHOOK_SECRET}`) {
    return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
  }

  try {
    const payload = await req.json();
    const { record } = payload;

    if (!record) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "No record in payload" }), { status: 400 });
    }

    const oldEmoji = STATUS_EMOJI[record.old_status] || "⚪";
    const newEmoji = STATUS_EMOJI[record.new_status] || "⚪";
    const dominoName = DOMINO_NAMES[record.domino_id] || `Domino ${record.domino_id}`;

    const message = [
      `${newEmoji} <b>Signal Alert</b>`,
      ``,
      `<b>Domino ${record.domino_id}:</b> ${dominoName}`,
      `<b>Signal:</b> ${record.signal_name}`,
      `<b>Status:</b> ${oldEmoji} ${record.old_status} → ${newEmoji} ${record.new_status}`,
      `<b>Trigger:</b> ${record.trigger_type}`,
      record.reason ? `<b>Reason:</b> ${record.reason}` : null,
      ``,
      `<i>${new Date(record.changed_at).toLocaleString("en-US", { timeZone: "America/Chicago" })}</i>`,
    ].filter(Boolean).join("\n");

    const tgRes = await fetch(
      `https://api.telegram.org/bot${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/sendMessage`,
      {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          chat_id: TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,
          text: message,
          parse_mode: "HTML",
        }),
      }
    );

    const tgData = await tgRes.json();

    if (!tgData.ok) {
      console.error("Telegram error:", tgData);
      // TODO: email fallback via Resend
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: tgData }), { status: 500 });
    }

    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ ok: true, message_id: tgData.result.message_id }), {
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });

  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Alert function error:", err);
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: err.message }), { status: 500 });
  }
});
```

### Supabase Setup (manual — document these steps)

1. Deploy: `supabase functions deploy signal-alert --no-verify-jwt`
2. Set secrets:
   ```bash
   supabase secrets set TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_token
   supabase secrets set TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id
   supabase secrets set REDACTED
   ```
3. Create database webhook in Supabase Dashboard:
   - Table: `signal_history`
   - Events: `INSERT`
   - Type: Supabase Edge Functions
   - Function: `signal-alert`
   - Headers: `Authorization: Bearer {WEBHOOK_SECRET}`

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Edge Function deploys successfully with `supabase functions deploy`
- [ ] Inserting a row into `signal_history` triggers the function
- [ ] Telegram message received with correct formatting (emoji, domino name, signal, old→new status)
- [ ] Timezone shows Central Time (America/Chicago)
- [ ] Invalid webhook calls (wrong auth) return 401
- [ ] Function handles missing `record` gracefully

### Do NOT
- Implement the email fallback (mark as TODO for later)
- Create or modify any client-side code
- Create Supabase tables
- Set up the Supabase project itself

